data.text:
Music fans are in for a treat as Nate Setto, KXNG Crooked and TMF Precha have joined forces and released their highly anticipated new single, "100 Million". The dynamic trio, known for their unique styles and chart-topping hits, have once again delivered a banger that has gotten listeners on their feet.

The single, which was released on all major streaming platforms on Friday, has already premiered on Hollywood Unlocked and garnered a lot of attention, making positive reviews from fans and critics alike. "100 Million" is a high-energy track that showcases the talents of TMF Precha, Nate Setto and KXNG Crooked, with catchy lyrics and a beat that has listeners vibing along.

KXNG Crooked, former member of “Slaughterhouse”, a rap group that consisted of Royce 5’9″, Joe Budden, and Joell Ortiz, is no stranger to success in the music industry. With hits alongside of "Russ" and "Eminem", he has solidified his place as a top artist in the hip-hop scene. TMF Precha, a rising Georgia native in the rap game and founder of Now Entertainment, has been making waves with unapologetic and bold lyrics, earning him a loyal fan base and collaborations with big names in the industry.

The collaboration between the three artists on "100 Million" is a testament to their versatility and ability to create music that resonates with audiences from different backgrounds. The single is a perfect blend of Pop and rap, showcasing the unique talents of all three artists. Fans can also expect another single by Nate Setto & TMF Precha titled “Monster” to be released in the coming weeks.

"100 Million" is a must-listen for all music lovers and is now available on all streaming platforms. With the combined star power of Nate Setto, TMF Precha, and KXNG Crooked, this single has proven to be a hit and on repeat for many.
